B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions, Article Quantities in Each)                                                             FY 2027     FY 2027     FY 2027
                                                                                                                     FY 2025    FY 2026      Base        OOC         Total
Support NAMRU-D Advanced Development activities in areas including biosensors, oximetry, human
performance, night vision, adaptive displays, anthropometry, neck/back pain, and hearing protection that are
aligned to aeromedical priorities and target transition programs.

Continue development of Mask Sensors and Operator State Monitoring systems including evaluation of
prototype warning modalities for range of use cases including cognitive degradation, physiological impairment,
task saturation, and / or mishap adjudication. Verify and validate performance and refine component and
subsystem capability as required.

Advance Aircrew Systems for current/future missions while addressing Aircrew Endurance. Advancements
will address obsolete and out-of-date aircrew systems that no longer meet and/or address current fleet needs/
requirements. Areas include: back and neck pain/injury; reducing bulk and weight of aircrew systems; acute and
chronic injury mechanisms; aircrew protection and performance; potential longer recovery times in water; polar
missions; and pre-conditioning.
