FY 2027 Base Plans:
Continue to explore, test, and develop design concepts of effective human-machine interfaces for crewed,
uncrewed human/autonomy teaming. Mature brain-computer/brain-machine interface technology and
biocybernetic system capability. Continue to advance operator state monitoring to detect physiological and
cognitive degradation, hydration/dehydration, and fatigue for mishap prevention and adjudication. Continue
to integrate data from USN/USMC Anthropometry study into updated aircraft and clothing/PPE acquisition
requirements to more accurately reflect future aircrew target population for improved aircrew clothing/equipment
fit and tariffing. Continue development of physical and digital human modeling capabilities to assess and quantify
aircrew musculoskeletal disorder (MSD) risk. Mature enhanced noise dosimetry technology to determine
deficiencies and effects of current protection. Continue to mature digital sensors and displays, and optics to
meet the long-term night vision requirements of Naval aircrew. Conduct evaluation of prototype USN/USMC
Embedded Care/Aircrew Conditioning Programs to inform fleet and program office transition plans. Continue to
partner with NAMRU-D and other performers to access unique subject matter expertise, laboratory capabilities,
and relevant APCD technologies in areas including but not limited to advanced biosensors, dehydration,
physiological/cognitive degradation detection and notification, digital vision technology, and chronic MSD
mitigation strategy development.
