FY 2027 Base Plans:
Continue evaluation and refinement of Human Body Models (HBM) for acute and chronic musculoskeletal
disorder (MSD) mitigation. Transition from non-biofidelic Anthropomorphic Test Devices (ATDs) to biofidelic
digital twins. Fully incorporate USN/USMC Anthropometry study results. Continue maturation and qualification
of clear Laser Eye Protection (LEP) visor technology, improved mobile aircrew restraint systems, vibration
isolation systems across all Rotary Wing/Tilt-Rotor (RW/TR) platforms, miniaturized ANR in-ear hearing
protection with improved speech intelligibility. Continue development/refinement/transition of RW VIPER restraint
system for additional use cases i.e., Search and Rescue (SAR) swimmer. Spiral development and transition of
aircrew and maintainer clothing and PPE systems appropriate for extended survival in extreme environment (i.e.,
INDOPACOM, Polar). Continue to partner with NAMRU-D and other performers to access unique subject matter
expertise, laboratory capabilities, and relevant APCD technologies in areas including but not limited to vibration
isolation seating systems, acute and chronic MSD Human Body Model development and validation, and arctic
environment capability gap closure.
