Description: HD-732D description: The HD-732D is a portable, AC-powered air particle sampler. It's operated
by NNPP activities to monitor for the presence of airborne radioactive contamination. The HD-732D is used to
draw a standardized volume of air through a filter paper, which traps airborne particulate. The filter paper is then
read by a separate radiation detector to determine the presence and quantity of airborne contamination.

