FY 2027 Base Plans:
In FY2027, the program will accelerate iterative development and testing of Automated Target Recognition
(ATR) algorithms for Rapid Area Detection (RAD). Key priorities include maturing the Machine Learning
Operations (MLOps) pipeline for production readiness, enhancing algorithm workflow capabilities at the tactical
edge, integrating onto additional sUAS platforms, and delivering a Minimum Viable Capability Release for both
the algorithm and MLOps platforms. Both disrupt and precision aim/render safe requirement CDD annex to
the Standoff Render Safe and Disrupt (SRSD) base requirement will be validated and enter the engineering,
manufacturing, and development phase of the acquisition process. Integration of EOD unmanned sensors and
payloads will continue development to meet the RAD and SRSD capability solution. The Access Buried Munition
CDD will be validated establishing a formal Joint Program of Record.
