Description: The FF(X) is a small blue water surface combatant, producible in volume, designed to fit within
the Golden Fleet's High/Low fleet architecture, focusing on surface warfare and command and control of
unmanned vessels. This effort initiates systems engineering and platform integration activities required to mature
the Frigate's C4I, Combat, and Aviation system suites. Combat System (CS) development activities focus
on ensuring the platform meets required combat capability through integration of key sensors and weapons,
including the SPS 77 radar, the MK48 Mod 2 Gun Weapon System and the Rolling Airframe Missile (RAM)
system. These efforts include hardware and software integration, interface development, and verification of
Combat System functionality within the ship's warfare architecture. The program will mature the integrated
Warfare System baseline to support upcoming integration and test events, validate interoperability among
warfare elements, and ensure the platform can effectively counter a broad range of current and emerging
threats.

