FY 2026 Plans:
Initiated systems engineering and platform integration efforts for C4I, Combat, and Aviation systems. Supported
Combat System (CS) development to ensure platform combat capability, including integration of the SPS 77
radar and Rolling Airframe Missile (RAM) system into the Combat System. Funding supports SPS 77 radar
integration activities to meet Frigate requirements. Advanced the Integrated Warfare System baseline to
enable integration and test events that evaluated platform performance across all mission areas. Implemented
additional cybersecurity and information assurance measures across the Warfare System and C4I suite to
address current and emerging threats.
FY 2027 Base Plans:
Continue systems engineering and platform integration efforts for C4I, Combat, and Aviation systems. Begin
System Qualification Testing (SQT) of the Combat Management System (CMS) and initiate Combat System
Integration (CSI) Testing to verify system functionality, interoperability, and readiness for integration into the total
ship combat system architecture. Coordinate with PAE RAS to enable integration pathways of the FF(X) with
MUSV and other unmanned systems to support "plug and play" accommodations for future unmanned systems.
Initiate Flight Upgrade planning activities to support a comprehensive capability increase for the FF(X) class
including evaluation, planning, and management of future transition from Atalanta Weapon System (ATwS)
to the Integrated Combat System (ICS) and increased integration with unmanned capabilities. This effort will
establish the technical, operational, and integration foundations required to define, assess, and implement a
new Flight configuration. Continue planning to support Support Combat System (CS) development to ensure
platform combat capability, including integration of the SPS 77 radar and Rolling Airframe Missile (RAM) system
into the Combat System. Continue SPS 77 radar integration activities to meet Frigate requirements. Mature the
integrated Warfare System baseline to support integration and test events that assess platform performance
across all mission areas. Implement additional cybersecurity and information assurance measures across the
Warfare System and C4I suite to address current and emerging threats.
FY 2027 OOC Plans:
N/A
