Description: Complete high-level planning to develop the FF(X) Master Test Strategy (MTS) to capture all
required test and evaluation activities planned for a Middle Tier Acquisition - Rapid Fielding ship program.
Conduct FF(X) test and evaluation planning to develop new program test requirements and documentation in
support of Early Integration Testing, Developmental Testing (DT) and Operational Testing (OT). Review of
Top-Level Requirements and engagement with the Navy Operational Test Agency in developing the Integrated
Evaluation Framework for the FF(X) ship class.

Test planning to include testing in support of Live Fire Test and Evaluation (LFT&E) modeling and small-scale
empirical testing to support efforts to model and assess survivability for the FF(X) class. Plan for coordination,
development, and alignment of resources to conduct Early Integration Testing and Cybersecurity Assessments
risk reduction efforts. Plan for assessing and developing early testing activities using existing land-based test
sites with selected systems to be fielded on the FF(X). Develop testing schedules and resource requirement
timelines to support later integration and certification testing. Plan and execute in coordination with the Navy
Operational Test Agency, execute Developmental Test Assist Design Review.

FY 2026 Plans:
Planned live-fire tests in support of generating empirical LFT&E survivability data for verification, validation, and
accreditation of multiple LFT&E survivability models. Results from these events identify additional LFT&E efforts
required for FF(X) class. Planned events included test execution, Modeling and Simulation (M&S) planning, and
material procurement for LFT&E testing efforts. Development of FF(X) test requirements focused on obtaining
data to reduce future at-sea testing requirements. Conduct system integration assessments associated with the
Combat System with other Warfare System selected for fielding on FF(X) ships.

Coordinated and planned Developmental Test Assist Design Review event for an early assessment of the FF(X)
class CONOPS, preliminary ship design documentation, planned mission critical systems hardware and software
versions and how they are to be integrated into the ship design, manning, training plans, and planned platform
employment in the fleet.
FY 2027 Base Plans:
Execute live-fire tests in support of generating empirical LFT&E survivability data for verification, validation,
and accreditation of multiple LFT&E survivability models. Conduct Cyber Range testing to assess system
performance in a representative operational cyber environment and to validate the system's ability to operate
securely under realistic threat conditions. Conduct early integration testing to evaluate initial system interactions.
