Developed a new functionality (software supporting data structure and migration of current data) within
Ordinance Information System (OIS) that provides visibility of serialized assets use and requirements.

Identification of at-risk platforms and implementing a reverse engineering/additive manufacturing program to
mitigate these issues.

FY 2026 Plans:
Due to weapon system obsolescence being viewed as one of the biggest readiness degraders for the Navy
Supply Chain mission, identification of at-risk platforms and implementing a reverse engineering/additive
manufacturing program was re-established in FY 2026.

Reverse Engineering of Technical Data Packages ($472K)
Funding is requested to support research and development related to reverse engineering Navy Supply
platforms which have been identified as either unsupported (no known or available source) or current support is
posing a risk to fleet readiness.

Funding will be used for a small business to reverse engineer/reverse manufacture an item and develop a
technical data package for future fleet requirements.
FY 2027 Base Plans:
N/A
