Description: Directed Energy Testing Against Missiles (DETAM) activities under Program Element (PE)
0603925N focus on system-level testing and evaluation (T&E) exercises on land and in a maritime environment.
The test campaign will leverage the Laser Weapon Testbed (LWT) and other directed energy assets. Testing
will involve surrogate targets in different defensive scenarios to assess system reliability and lethality to bolster
Naval understanding of laser weapon effectiveness against present-day and next generation threats. Moreover,
lethality models and simulations (M&S) will be supported by the large-scale test campaign. DETAM test design
will focus on lethality model validation and evaluating High Energy Laser (HEL) technologies to provide better
weapon systems to the warfighter. The data-driven approach will assess HEL weapon lethality in Naval-relevant
operational environments while also providing a testbed to evaluate new advanced components for all HEL
weapon sub-systems. DETAM will provide a T&E solution to the Counter Anti-ship Cruise Missile (C-ASCM)
operational challenge while enabling the Navy to rapidly integrate a fleet-ready HEL weapon.

