Autosuspends effort will develop software improvements for several key EMALS Computer Software Configuration Items (CSCIs) that will mitigate the EMALS
Autosuspends associated with faults and communication dropouts, which terminates the launch process and causes delays to launch operations. These software
improvements will significantly lessen the number of experienced Autosuspends and improve CVN launch operations in order to meet the operational need.

Development of a software maintenance laptop provides organizational level support of EMALS software. The current procedure requires onboard engineering support
in order to reduce troubleshooting and Mean Time To Repair (MTTR).

Catapult Status Dashboard (CSD) development will provide enhanced user situational awareness, improving EMALS operational efficiency. The current EMALS primary
operational station equipment, the Maintenance Workstation (MWS), was developed only for maintenance and does not adequately support user awareness of EMALS
launch operations.

The Windows 10 End of Life transition will enhance future EMALS readiness by upgrading the Operating System. Windows OS is responsible for the functionality of the
EMALS System, including all communications between the system and Fleet operators and maintainers. The OS upgrade will address Windows End of Life issues and
cyber vulnerabilities ensuring continued EMALS readiness and sustained operations.

The EMALS Server and PC-104 computers will be redesigned in order to address hardware obsolescence issues. The redesign includes both hardware and software
required to integrate the new components into the EMALS system. The Servers and PC-104 computers are critical control and communication components for EMALS
operations and are currently unprocurable to support Ford Class Carriers.

