 of the following three components: MINEnet Global (MNG), MINEnet Tactical (MNT), and Minefield Planning (MFP). MINEnet Global is a shore-based website that
 provides MIW waterspace awareness functionality to support Navy non-MIW forces. MINEnet Global provides downloadable reference databases, MIW reference
 publications and links to MIW information. The MINEnet Tactical component is a software application which provides MCM tactical planning, situational awareness and
 post mission evaluation capabilities. Minefield Planning is a tactical software application which provides commanders the ability to plan and assess offensive, defensive,
 and protective minefields based on oceanographic and mine performance data and user specified objectives. Depending on user need, MEDAL EA is networked or
 stand-alone and is either deployed on dedicated laptop computers or installed on the unit's/command's native computer resources.

5) MIW Integrated Synthetic Trainer (MIST) will provide integrated phase training for MIW staffs in end-to-end MCM scenarios. This tool will provide the capability to train
MIW staffs against near peer threats.

