A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The Mine Warfare Planning and Analysis project consists of two projects, the Mine Warfare and Environmental Decision Aids Library Enterprise Architecture (MEDAL
EA) and the Mine Warfare Integrated Synthetic Trainer (MIST). MEDAL EA is the U.S. Navy's single MIW tactical decision support system for integrated mission
planning, evaluation, and situational awareness. It provides mine warfare planning and evaluation tools and databases to mine countermeasures (MCM) commanders
and is employed at the unit level to perform MCM sortie planning and evaluation. MEDAL EA is a family of systems, comprised of the following three components:
MINEnet Global (MNG), MINEnet Tactical (MNT), and Minefield Planning (MFP). MINEnet Global is a shore-based website that provides MIW waterspace awareness
functionality to support Navy non-MIW forces. MINEnet Global provides downloadable reference databases, MIW reference publications and links to MIW information.
The MINEnet Tactical component is a software application which provides MCM tactical planning, situational awareness and post mission evaluation capabilities.
Minefield Planning is a tactical software application which provides commanders the ability to plan and assess offensive, defensive, and protective minefields based on
oceanographic and mine performance data and user specified objectives. Depending on user need, MEDAL EA is networked or stand-alone and is either deployed on
dedicated laptop computers or installed on the unit's/command's native computer resources. Mine Warfare Integrated Synthetic Trainer (MIST) is a synthetic training aid
that enables trainers to lead MIW staff and Warfare Tactics Instructors (WTIs) through end-to-end MCM simulations.

